            "widgets": [
              {
                "id": {
                  "value": "d148542d-21e8-41cc-be96-41c6205ec106"
                },
                "title": "Dashboard Guide",
                "definition": {
                  "markdown": {
                    "markdownText": "# Agave Contract & Synchronisation Health\n\nThis dashboard uses Agave configuration snapshots attached to Clearent deployment Events.\n\n## Available now\n- Agave deployment adoption and optional-snapshot coverage\n- Governed versus continuous configuration mode\n- Refresh interval\n- Provider-record, mapped-field and template counts\n- Application-level configuration trends and recent snapshots\n\n## Telemetry boundary\nThese are **deployment-time contract snapshots**. Continuous mode is a configuration value, not evidence that a synchronisation ran. API-call volume, synchronisation success/failure, duration and freshness require a future dedicated Agave synchronisation event contract.\n\nThe optional five-field suffix is all-or-nothing and may be absent when the Kubernetes Event note would exceed 1,024 UTF-8 bytes."
                  }
                }
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "options": {
          "internal": {}
        }
      },
